rComments: Not the prof for me. She doesnt let you in if youre late and she just repeats the textbook. The exams are not fair and overall just a really bad experience for me

Experienced Prof who posts all her slides and lecture audios online! So you can afford not going to class! If you're taking accounting for the first time, highly recommend going to class and tutorials regularly! Good Luck!

The pacing of her lectures isn't the best; she also likes Dollarama. The resources are there for you to do well; make sure to do her sample problems to practice for exams. Some of the questions are taken straight from there. Prepare some notes before class since she doesn't spend too much time explaining things in the textbook.

This is honestly the one review you need to listen to. Her lectures weren't that bad she honeslty broke down concepts nicely. Read the textbook!! She will put little fluff from chapter 1 to throw you off. Her office hours are useless seek the TA's and do all the practice! This course is about basics, master those and you're good. Do past midterms!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Test heavy']

rComments: Easy class if you have done accounting in high school this is an easy 4.0 don't listen to the negative posts, you will be more than prepared for this. If not just read some of the text book to refresh your memory. However, I do agree that her lectures are very boring but that's because I've taken accounting in high school.

Professor Seguin has a distinct style when she teaches. Her classes aren't very dynamic but rather structured. You are expected to read the book, make notes, and do the problems. MyAccountingLab helps as well. TAs have no office hours for this course, so you'll have to reach her for help. Overall, she's not difficult but be ready to do your share.
Horrible. She doesnt give any constructive criticism, is condescending and would steer clear away!!

She goes through the material quite fast but if you keep up with your readings and you keep practicing, then it should be an easy class to ace. She  gives you so much room to practice, and is very straightforward with what she expects from the class. She answers all questions asked during the lecture, and she does  not leave something unexplained.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She is an amazing professor, gives many chances for students to ask questions as she teaches. Teaches for half the lecture and takes up textbook problems for the other half. Tests, so easy, simply make an income statement and balance sheet. She can seem mean but is actually very caring and super helpful during office hours.  Posts all powerpoints.
She really wants her students to succeed, she may go a little fast but if you keep up with the homework and readings you will definitely get a good grade. For tests, practise using past tests.

She doesn't like to answer questions during lectures, instead ridicules students for not reading the textbook and already understanding it. She is monotone and does not care about her student's grades. She marks extremely difficult and gives no part marks for even trying. Also, accounting is difficult as is, and she's not friendly or approachable.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework']

rComments: most ruthless, insensitive, and cold professor in the university. Has no warmth or care for students.
worst professor ever.

She is a great professor. Very clear and to the point. Her lecture slides for the entire term are already there for you from day 1 of the course. Never miss the readings or forget to do the homework. VERY IMPORTANT TO PASSING. Tests are not as easy as one would think so study and also, if you've taken accounting before, don't be overconfident.

I found this course to be quite easy. The lectures are pretty long though. Reading the book, and doing past tests and exams are ways of getting a good grade. Test questions are much more different and difficult than class discussion and tutorial problems. I think doing exams and past tests provide better practice for tests and exams.
Catherine Sequin is a good prof, I like that she goes through accounting examples in the lecture. It facilitates my learning and I can ask questions if I don't understand something.

I believe this professor makes an effort to teach well, however she is one of the worst professors I've ever had at UTM. She is very strict and completely heartless when it comes to small mistakes. Make sure you don't defer tests for her MGT120 course or you will have to do a presentation in front of her and prof Baily, with no rubric to follow.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: She is really good. Manage to get 99 in this course by just reading the book. tutorial is useless.

Just attend every lecture, tutorials are somewhat useless in my opinion. She is helpful when asking questions but her answers are somewhat unclear. Overall everyone I know got a 90+ in her course and I received a 97 - Should have been a 99 if TA marked my first midterm properly.
She is an excellent professor!! Easy midterms, but watch out for the finals.
Very strict prof. Goes really fast through the material. I aced all the quizzes but did HORRIBLE on the midterms - nothing like them and the exam was SOO HARD.

Good prof, explains things clearly and always helpful if you need a hand. I had no accounting background but left class feeling like I understood stuff..keeping up with the reading and online quizzes is very crucial for a good grade in this course!! Work hard, and it'll pay off
Good prof. Do all the homework go to every class and tutorial and you should have no problem. The final exam was so easy i think i got over 90% on it.  Can easily get 4.0 GPA in this course
She explains the requirment very clearly. For mgt120 make sure to read the text. She is a nice lady I would say.

She seems a bit too all work, no play sorta thing. She honestly goes a bit too fast, I had an accounting background but I wonder what people who have nothing can keep up with her. You can ace all the problems done in class and tutorial, but believe when I say this, mid terms and exams -NOTHING LIKE THEM. Totally different and was tough..

This teacher is garbage, she tries to rush her lectures n finish the material in one hour, n then does easy examples from the book for another hour. As a student who had not taken account before, reading the textbook is a must, i was doing good like 70+. But the tests n exams r HARD, the exam dropped me to 60. Now i hav to take this course again
EASIEST COMMERCE FIRST YEAR COURSE EVER!! MAKE SURE YOU DO THE READINGS AND YOU'RE GOLDEN...lectures and tutorials are useless but text is important.

She's a really nice person, but absolutely terrible at teaching this course. She has little to no actual knowledge of the material and is in constant need of her textbook or her notes to answer basic questions (sometimes of material that she just covered 5 minutes prior to the question).

She was terrible. Basically she was an audio player for textbook. Does not know how to teach without referring to text book. If you know some accounting and wanting to advance, do not take it with her. She will take the fun out of accounting and your life.

Way too many hours are required for the course! I had an 88 on the first midterm, and an 80 on the second. Ended up with a 63 after the final exam, after solid studying.... Disappointed thats for sure. Watch out for the last exam...
She has done a good job in teaching this first year accounting course. Fair course!

personally, i dont like accounting, but that doesn't make her to be a bad prof ^^. If u are new to accounting, u need to catch up her pace, because she is a bit quick. Tests are harder than average level, so u have to study.

You dont need a HS background to do well in this course.Attend the lectures because most of the theory part of the exam comes from the lecture and slides.Practise previous years question papers as MC is often repeated.Regular work is required..and she often provides 'flashbacks' of the last class during her lecture. She emailes back really quickly.

The most boring course ever.(MGT120).She has no enthusiasm,and makes accounting boring,and makes it seem useless,even though its actually very important.Her tests are fair,but are extremely tricky,and hard.Shes always there to help though.unless u have a thing for accounting or are passionate about it, dont expect more than an 80.

the midterms were fairly easy and straight forward if prepared ahead however the exam was extremely time-consuming and somewhat tricky. the prof answers emails fast. is not a mark booster due to the final exam!!!!!

you HAVE to keep up with your work!! I didn't have any accounting experience.. so I had to spend way too many hours on that course to get a 70%.. but it feels worth it at the end! The tests are mega hard.. nothing ever balances.. so make sure you know ur concepts inside out!

Good traits include loud and clear voice (she doesn't need to use any sound device for a large class), and a very logical way of explaining things. Bad traits? I can't think of any aside from her lack of enthusiasm which I don't really mind at all. Great prof overall. I'm sure she'd become a drill sergeant if she joins the army.
She's not very enthusiastic so you don't feel like ever going to class.  Her tests are super hard! And she's quite intimidating.

She appears to be rather intimidating but is actually pretty clear when it comes to teaching the material. The first half of lecture, she regurgitates the text, the second half, she takes up homework problems. Very helpful! Read the text and do the assigned work! Go to tutorial and keep on top of things. Tests and exams are EXTREMELY difficult!

I was scared as hell about accounting before going into the course but with this prof. I ended up really appreciating it. Very clear in explaining. Very predictable course ie. you KNOW what's going to be on the tests. The course is made to be accounting for people that are DEFINITELY not going to be accountants  so not so much detail and technicali
Better than Connie REED!
If you've taken accounting before, the course is fairly easy. Just do the assigned work, and you'll get a good mark. Lectures are really boring though.

She is strict, fierce, and the no-nonsense type. She doesnt seem to have much enthusiasm for what she's teaching, but she does teach clearly and responsibly. To do well, make sure you read before going to class and do all the assigned questions. The course is very predicatable if you do the necessary work.

Terrible!!! She gave something we never learned on the exam~~ well.. maybe because I have never learned accounting before.. In general, she is not helpful. I dont see the point of going to her class. The textbook does a much better job on explaining the concepts!

I had no accounting before and got 85 with little studying. At the university level, if you can't keep up with Seguin, I don't think you belong here. The concepts are easy and she even does textbook problems IN CLASS! Always do her MC's last. Some of her MC's can very well be a short answer Q that takes up 20% of the test.
this lady sucks

i agree...i had no accounting background and i got 66 which was was 12% lower than my 2nd lowest course, and 22% lower than my best course. Ppl with background, i knew, were having a much easier time. But all in all im just glad its over and i dont have to worry of it anymore.
people from H.S with a good understanding... ( from a few post before)    I second that!
doesnt seem to know what shes talkin about or how to use chalk
very helpful
A really good prof...I had no accounting background but did well because she teaches very clearly.  Tests are a little challenging, but if you know the concept you should be fine.

people from H.S with a good understanding of accounting breezed through this course, many people who have never taken accounting before really struggled. at the beginning of the year, she says on avg, pp who have never taken accting before get higher marks on average then those who have. LIES!!!!
Explains material well and knows a lot about subject. Helps students beyond regular class time in extra tutorials and office hours. Tests are very fair.
GOOD TEACHER BUT HARD..
good prof. in first yr~
she is so good! best prof you can get in first year!
Never took acc before. Before the first term test, I attended every single lecture, then got B. After that, I never went to class again and managed to get A in the course.  The final exam is tricky.

she's the worse you can ever get. she just reads off lecture notes from other professors as if no one can READ and surely she doesn't know what she's talking about. but too bad it seems like no one can get rid of her (cuz she's the only one teaching) GL
She's like a carbon copy of [Dame] Judi Dench seen in the James Bond movies. Yeah so there you go.

The course is really fast paced, so if you slack off, catching up is a nightmare. Tests are application-based so memorizing the textbook is not enough! You have to practice. Seguin is fair when she warns about the course being tough. She's helpful 1 on 1.
okay prof, okay course, but the course is kinda hard.
